     2→//! Pagination, repository abstraction and a concrete implementation for
     3→//! Ledger Entries.
     4→//
     5→//! This module is **self–contained** and depends only on widely–used crates
     6→//! (`sqlx`, `serde`, `validator`, `chrono`, …).  It is written to be dropped
     7→//! into the LedgerLink Nexus code-base without further modification.
     8→//
     9→//! High-level responsibilities
    10→//! ---------------------------
    11→//! 1. Parse & validate incoming pagination parameters
    12→//! 2. Offer a *view-model* friendly `Paginated<T>` envelope
    13→//! 3. Expose a generic `PaginatedRepository` trait (Command/Query separation)
    14→//! 4. Provide a production-grade Postgres implementation for ledger entries
    15→//! 5. Supply rich error reporting + structured tracing instrumentation
    16→//! 6. Attach *caching hints* so the API-Gateway can make smart decisions
    17→
    18→#![allow(clippy::module_name_repetitions)]
    19→
    20→use std::collections::HashMap;
    21→use std::fmt;
    22→
    23→use async_trait::async_trait;
    24→use chrono::{DateTime, Utc};
    25→use serde::{Deserialize, Serialize};
    26→use sqlx::{postgres::PgQueryResult, PgPool, Postgres, QueryBuilder, FromRow};
    27→use thiserror::Error;
    28→use tracing::{error, instrument};
